{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XvQdNdqmSURdaEXF8APCmP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ETL pipeline completed successfully. Here's a complete summary of the diagnosis and fix:\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause\n\n**Severe data skew in Stage 3 (GROUP BY user_id):**\n- `user_id=999` holds **50,000 of 100,000 records** (~50%)\n- **Skew ratio: 500x** (average per user: 100 records; hot key: 50,000)\n- Original executor memory of **256MB** was far too small — all 50,000 records for `user_id 999` got assigned to a single task/partition, exhausting the executor heap → `OutOfMemoryError`\n\n## Fix Applied (Options B + C combined)\n\nThe fix in `etl-job.yaml` addresses both the memory ceiling and the skew distribution:\n\n| Setting | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `spark.executor.memory` | `256m` | `1g` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled` | not set | `true` |\n| `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled` | not set | `true` |\n\n- **Increased executor memory to 1g** gives headroom for the hot partition\n- **AQE + skewJoin splitting** automatically detects the skewed partition and splits it into smaller sub-tasks so no single executor gets overwhelmed\n\n## Result\n\nThe ETL job completed successfully in 114 seconds (`COMPLETIONS: 1/1`, exit code 0), with `spark_etl_pipeline_verified` printed at the end."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1927,"cache_read_input_tokens":37041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1927},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"763046a9-74cb-423e-85d2-36e84cb8d8a4","uuid":"31248833-f742-43c8-af9b-13296d4c58f1","request_id":"req_011Cc6jaZHFXQooSsFM6NL1z"}
